FIRSTdatabase.name: FIRST - Run Less, Run Faster Furman University
FIRSTdatabase.note: Instructions Glossary: The instructions syntax is strict, case-sensitive, and unforgiving to user error. Each instruction starts with a week number and a keyrun number, divided by a space. The workout steps start after another space and end at the end of the line. Steps are separated by # or ). Predefined steps have special keywords like warmup or cooldown. Simple steps have the format - distance unit@pace-name. For example 3.5 mile@RI. The space between the distance and the unit is mandatory. distance is a real number. Repetition steps have the format - REPx(list of steps). For example 2x(3.5 mile@RI). The - x character is mandatory. Repetition steps can be nested recursively. REP is an integer. Distance unit names are m, km, mile, or ft. pace-names for repetitive runs are 400m, 600m, 800m, 1000m, 1200m, 1600m, and 2000m. pace-names for tempo runs are short, mid, long, and easy Special pace-names are RI for Rest Interval and RP for Race Pace. Also RP+10, RP+15, RP+20, RP+30, RP+45, and RP+60. All paces and the predefined steps are determined by the program and are calculated based on user input.
